<div class="definition" id="definition-MI" acro="MI" titletext="Matrix Inverse">
<h5 class="definition">
<span class="type">Definition </span><span class="acro">MI</span> <span class="titletext"> Matrix Inverse</span>
</h5>
<p>Suppose $A$ and $B$ are square matrices of size $n$ such that $AB=I_n$ and $BA=I_n$.  Then $A$ is <em class="term">invertible</em> and $B$ is the <em class="term">inverse</em> of $A$.  In this situation, we write $B=\inverse{A}$.</p>
